        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         My pet always responds while casting.<BR>It won't accept hotkeyed commands though. You have to actually type in the pet command while casting.</P><P>If you type fast enough it's great for STing a mob and backing off your pet in time. Just start casting then type /pet back off and wait until the casting time is almost done and then hit your enter key. It will back off every time (unless ST is resisted).</P><P>You can do the same thing for attacks. Start casting - type your command and your pet will be at the mob when the spell hits.</P><P>Charsis Soulshifter<BR>Lvl 59 Defiler<BR>Rodcet Nife<BR><Warlords of Wrath><BR><img src="http://shakes-net.com/pictures/charsisanim.gif" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
